[SN]TITLE[SN]
Game designer shares his top tips

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
These days, you don't need a huge team and a massive budget to develop a hit video game.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
21 August 2015 Last updated at 09:48 BST
Game designer Arran Langmead reaches a global audience from his Southampton flat.
His latest project is a game called Bears Can't Drift - a kart racing game which he hopes to launch for both the Sony Playstation Network and the Steam games store over the next couple of months.
He shared his top tips for aspiring game developers with the BBC Tech Tent programme.
